CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 6, 1957, pg. 7 reads: "Graduates' Reception - Trinity AME Sunday School sponsored a reception for its members who were recent graduates of junior and senior high school. Seated, left to right: Jean Brown, Sandra Williams, Patricia Milton and Mary Stevens.  Second row: Roy Ponders, Betty Wilkins, Mrs. Daisy Johnson, Miss Florene A. Cherry, of the Pittsburgh Urban League, Beverly Sewell and Mrs. Alma A. Polk, sponsor.  Back row: James Bussey, superintendent, and Daniel Ponder.  The Rev. A. A. Nelson, pastor, is not shown in picture. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Graduates and Trinity AME Sunday school members, seated from left: Jean Brown, Sandra Williams, Patricia Milton, Mary Stevens; second row: Roy Ponders, Betty Wilkins, Daisy Johnson, Florene A. Cherry of Pittsburgh Urban League, Beverly Sewell, and Alma A. Polk, sponsor; back row: James Bussey, superintendent, and Daniel Ponder, posed in interior with two toned walls and wooden folding chairs
